The course provides an overview of conceptualizing unique interplay between individual, social, situational, and systemic factors that determine specialized needs in a psychological intervention related to athletic or professional performance.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to aquire the principles and methods of case formulation in sport and performance psychology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will be able to 1. explain importance of a comprehensive assessment of the athlete or performer in case formulation process  2. outline the process of organizing and conceptualizing assessment material in case formulation 3. classify issues and challenges related to career development, interpersonal relationships, organizational demands, and mental health of athletes and performers 4. integrate assessment, conceptualization and classification in the case formulation  5. describe intervention planning based on case formulation in sport and performance psychlogy
